You are working on ralph-engine, an autonomous AI development loop engine written in Go.

Read AGENTS.md for full coding standards (EARS syntax), architecture, commands, and quality checklist. AGENTS.md is the single source of truth — follow it exactly.

Key rules (EARS format):
- ALL code, comments, docs, tests SHALL be in English.
- Tests SHALL be written BEFORE implementation (TDD).
- `go vet` → `go test ./... -count=1` → `go build ./cmd/ralph-engine/` SHALL pass before any commit.
- Code SHALL compile on Linux, macOS, and Windows (use build tags for OS-specific code).
- Commit messages SHALL follow conventional format: `type(scope): description`
- Library code SHALL return errors with context via `fmt.Errorf`. SHALL NOT panic.
- Functions SHALL have ≤ 20 lines, ≤ 3 parameters.
- Exported symbols SHALL have Godoc comments ending with a period.
